    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 8, 2026\n\n---\n\n## ⛽ Iran Blinked. The Strait Opens. Oil Drops 8%.\n\nHours before Trump's Tuesday night deadline, the U.S. and Iran agreed to a two-week ceasefire — and oil markets had their best day in months.\n\n- **The deal:** Iran agreed to allow \"safe passage through the Strait of Hormuz via coordination with Iran's Armed Forces\" for two weeks. Trump suspended bombing. Pakistan invited both delegations to Islamabad on Friday, April 10. Iran declared \"victory.\" Trump called Iran's 10-point counter-proposal \"a workable basis on which to negotiate.\"\n- **The market:** U.S. crude slid 8%, from $117 intraday to ~$103 per barrel after the announcement. The UN Security Council separately failed to adopt a draft resolution on the Hormuz crisis — a vote now rendered largely symbolic.\n\n*Both sides declared victory. Oil is at $103. Nobody explain to them that only one of these statements can mean what they think it means.*\n\n**Sources:** [ABC News](https://abcnews.com/International/live-updates/iran-live-updates-casualties-reported-missile-strikes-israel/?id=131757074) | [NBC News](https://www.nbcnews.com/world/iran/live-blog/live-updates-iran-war-trump-deadline-hormuz-infrastructure-ceasefire-rcna267039) | [PBS](https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/irans-supreme-national-security-council-says-it-has-accepted-two-week-ceasefire-in-the-war)\n\n---\n\n## 🪖 France Is Building a War Economy. Literally. They Named It That.\n\nFrance presented its updated military planning law to the Council of Ministers today. The goal: quadruple drone stockpiles, double missile reserves, and prepare for a high-intensity conflict that European generals are now openly calling inevitable.\n\n- **The numbers:** An additional €8.5 billion for ammunition orders through 2030, bringing the total ammunition budget to €24.5 billion. Loitering munitions (kamikaze drones): +400%. AASM Hammer guided bombs: +240%. Aster and Mica missiles: +30%. The law goes to the National Assembly in May, the Senate in June.\n- **The context:** European military chiefs are publicly naming 2028–2029 as the potential window for conflict with Russia. France is doubling its defense budget faster than originally planned. The law was presented to Cabinet on April 8, 2026.\n\n*France is building a war economy and calling it a war economy. Points for honesty.*\n\n**Sources:** [Pravda EU](https://eu.news-pravda.com/ukraine/2026/04/03/183312.html) | [Your News](https://yournews.com/2026/04/04/6761104/france-drafts-war-economy-plan-to-expand-drone-and-missile/) | [Defense Magazine](https://www.defensemagazine.com/article/the-french-army-aims-at-four-new-priorities-france-to-double-its-defence-budget-faster)\n\n---\n\n## 💊 Trump's New Tariffs Hit Pharma at 100%. The Stock Market Is Not Okay.\n\nOne year after Liberation Day, Trump doubled down — and added pharmaceutical imports to the list, at rates up to 100%.\n\n- **The new architecture:** A 10% global baseline tariff under Section 122 replaced the IEEPA authority the Supreme Court struck down in February. New pharma tariffs up to 100% were announced April 2. The U.S. is generating $29 billion per month in tariff revenue. Retailers are absorbing it. Consumers will absorb the rest.\n- **The market:** The Nasdaq entered correction territory. Tech is hardest hit — Apple, Dell, and HP face 25–34% duties on goods made in China, Taiwan, and Vietnam. A single White House announcement now moves the S&P 500 by 1–2% intraday. This is considered normal.\n\n*(Cool. Great. Fine. Probably fine.)*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/03/trump-tariffs-trade-war-impact.html) | [Tax Foundation](https://taxfoundation.org/research/all/federal/trump-tariffs-trade-war/) | [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/4/2/trumps-tariffs-one-year-on-how-americans-are-paying-the-price)\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Congress Wants to Cut China Off From the Machines That Make the Chips\n\nThe MATCH Act would ban DUV lithography equipment exports to China — the tools that manufacture the chips that power the AI that everyone is currently panicking about.\n\n- **The bill:** Introduced April 2 by bipartisan Senate and House members. Full ban on exporting DUV lithography systems to China plus restrictions on maintenance and upgrades. Would coordinate controls with the Netherlands (ASML) and Japan (Canon, Nikon). It targets the manufacturing equipment, not the chips themselves.\n- **The problem:** ASML sold 70% of its DUV lithography systems to Chinese entities in 2024, under existing export controls. China's domestic AI chip market share is projected to hit 50% in 2026. The horse may already be out of the barn, but Congress is now very interested in the barn.\n\n*Closing the semiconductor barn door after the ASML has bolted.*\n\n**Sources:** [Open Data Science](https://opendatascience.com/house-introduces-match-act-to-tighten-ai-chip-export-controls/) | [FDD](https://www.fdd.org/analysis/2026/04/03/congress-targets-advanced-chip-making-equipment-to-stifle-chinese-progress-in-ai-race/) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/05/us-reportedly-considering-sweeping-new-chip-export-controls/)"
